<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN SOFTBALL TEAM BEATS UNLV BEFORE LOSING TO THE RAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RALPH NICHOLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For Coach Gary Torgeson, the Tournament of Champions offers an opportunity to 
see how his Cal State Northridge softball team will fare against Division I 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
Torgeson did not get much of a chance to preview the Lady Matadors on Friday, 
however, after CSUN's afternoon game against Sacramento State was rained out. 
</P>
<P>
In CSUN's morning game, pitcher Debbie Dickmann threw a 2-hit shutout to lead 
the host team to a 1-0 victory over Nevada Las Vegas in 8 innings. 
</P>
<P>
"We're not out here to lose, but I was actually more concerned with getting 
some games played so I could get a look at our personnel," Torgeson said. 
</P>
<P>
The coach liked what he saw against UNLV, especially the strong effort of 
Dickmann, a Division II All-American who was 22-4 with 17 shutouts last season. 
Dickmann allowed just 2 singles. 
</P>
<P>
Lisa Erickson scored the only run in the eighth. She reached base on a bunt 
single, advanced on another, then scored on a wild throw after a fielder's 
choice. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Matadors will play San Diego State this morning unless rain forces 
another cancellation. Only six of 12 games were completed Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Matadors will play San Francisco in a second game this afternoon. 
RALPH NICHOLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
