<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man accused of shooting his mother-in-law in a Clairemont doughnut shop 
pleaded not guilty to a murder charge Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Randy Geering, 36, previously was charged with attempted murder in the Sunday 
shooting of Audrey Erbe, 59, but the charge was amended when she died 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Erbe was shot just above the eye and was in a coma for several days. 
</P>
<P>
Geering's estranged wife, Diane Geering, was also at the doughnut shop, but hid 
in the bathroom when she saw Geering in the shop with a gun, Deputy Dist. Atty. 
Greg McClain said. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Municipal Judge Raymond Edwards Jr. rescheduled the preliminary 
hearing for March 2. He allowed the $200,000 bail to continue, even though the 
charge was amended. 
</P>
<P>
McClain said Geering had assaulted his ex-wife several times before the 
shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
