<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARCOS' RETURN URGED BY LAUREL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philippine Vice President Salvador Laurel said after a bedside visit with 
former President Ferdinand E. Marcos that he believes the exiled leader is near 
death and that he should be allowed to return to his homeland to die. 
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced from what I have seen and heard that the reports of his 
deteriorating condition and imminent death are accurate," Laurel said in a 
statement Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
"Now is the time for compassion and forgiveness in order to achieve much-needed 
unity among all Filipinos," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Laurel said he believes Marcos should be allowed to go home "to die." 
</P>
</TEXT>
