<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
 MEASLES OUTBREAK CLAIMS 2 CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An outbreak of measles among members of a Long Beach church has left two 
children dead, 12 hospitalized and two more sick at home. 
</P>
<P>
"I anticipate a few more cases," said Bob Salcido, senior epidemiologist with 
the Long Beach Department of Health and Human Services. "Usually it comes in 
waves." 
</P>
<P>
The 16 stricken children -- ranging in age from 6 months to 13 years -- are all 
of Samoan ancestry and associated with United Samoan Assembly of God in Long 
Beach, Salcido said. The two who died, he said, were ages 3 and 19 months. 
Salcido would not release the children's names. 
</P>
<P>
At least six of the stricken children had not been immunized against the 
disease, Salcido said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
