<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LOVER OF MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Max Laemmle, the Man Who Loved Movies, was a major force in Los Angeles film 
culture, not only for the films he presented but for his warm and generous 
collaboration with other film organizations. 
</P>
<P>
It was with the help of Laemmle (who died Jan. 20) that the American Film 
Institute was able to reorganize the Los Angeles International Film Festival in 
1987 (replacing Filmex) and present it at his Los Feliz Cinema. His 
collaboration with the AFI continued in specialized festivals at his Santa 
Monica Cinema devoted to European, British, U.S. independent and documentary 
films. He will be greatly missed. 
</P>
<P>
KEN WLASCHIN 
</P>
<P>
Director, AFI/LA FilmFest 
</P>
<P>
GARY McVEY 
</P>
<P>
Associate Director 
</P>
