<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARINARO'S THIRD GOAL GIVES LAZERS WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WICHITA, Kan. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hector Marinaro scored 3 goals, including the game-winner in overtime, to give 
the Lazers a 7-6 victory over the Wichita Wings in Major Indoor Soccer League 
action Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Goals by Victor Moreland and Mike Fox in the second period gave Wichita a 2-0 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
Marinaro's first goal made it 2-1, but Jean Willrich scored for the Wings to 
increase the lead to two again. 
</P>
<P>
The Lazers (13-12) narrowed the score on a goal by Mike Collins, but Chico 
Moreira scored for Wichita, putting the Wings ahead at the half, 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
Third-quarter goals by Bobby Joe Esposito and Steve Kinsey tied the score, 4-4. 
</P>
<P>
Marinaro's second goal of the game came early in the fourth quarter, and Los 
Angeles extended its lead on a shot by Gary Heale to 6-4. 
</P>
