<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cooper Cos. reported a $115-million fourth-quarter loss, compared to a loss of 
$4.8 million a year earlier. Sales fell to $160.2 million, down 9%. The quarter 
includes a $59-million provision for losses on a planned divestiture. The Palo 
Alto-based medical products firm posted a $207-million loss for the year, 
contrasted with net income of $52 million in 1987. Sales jumped to $611.31 
million, up 72%. Results aren't directly comparable, the firm said, because 
figures from Cooper Technicon are included in full-year 1988 results but are 
included only in the last four months of the previous year. 
</P>
