<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
SOUTH COAST LEAGUE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MISSION VIEJO STUNS IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jim Butchko scored 19 points, Greg Amaya had 16 and Eric Cramer 14 to lead 
Mission Viejo High School to a 64-50 South Coast League victory over 
fourth-ranked Irvine Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The Diablos (9-12 overall, 4-4 in league play) never trailed in the second half 
as they held Irvine's high-scoring duo, John Molle and Brian Allred, in check 
with tough man-to-man defense. Allred had 11 points and Molle 10. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine fell to 20-4 overall and 6-2 in league play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
