<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RANCHO ALAMITOS STAYS IN RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos High School got its best performance of the season when it 
needed it the most Friday night as the Vaqueros defeated Pacifica, 72-44, in a 
key Garden Grove League boys' basketball game at Rancho Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos (9-8, 7-4 in league play) moved to within striking range of 
third-place Pacifica (13-6, 8-3). La Quinta (15-5, 10-1) is first, one game 
ahead of Kennedy (16-7, 9-2) and two in front of Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
"This was a must-win for us if we were going to have any chance of catching 
Pacifica or anyone else for third place," Rancho Alamitos Coach Terry Munson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Vaqueros led, 21-17, at the end of the first quarter and outscored the 
Mariners, 15-5, to take a 36-22 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Lira scored 24 points and David Green 20 to lead Rancho Alamitos. Green 
also had 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
The Vaqueros dominated the inside game as Richard Pearce had 17 rebounds and 11 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos played a box-and-one defense on Pacifica's Dustin Bonham, who 
came into the game averaging 19.9 points. Bonham was held to 6 points by Rancho 
Alamitos' Jim Yarnell. Bill Maurer scored 10 points to lead Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 71, Los Amigos 51 -- Scott Campbell scored 26 points to lead host La 
Quinta (15-5, 10-1). Campbell, a 6-foot 5-inch senior, made 12 of 19 shots and 
had 10 rebounds. Scott Linck had 13 points and Bill Snyder 10 for the Aztecs. 
Snyder also had nine assists and Linck six. Carlos Palomino scored 18 points 
and David Pearlman 11 for Los Amigos (6-12, 4-7). 
</P>
</TEXT>
