<P>
PACIFIC COAST LEAGUE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TRABUCO HILLS CLINCHES SHARE OF TITLE, 78-59 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rick Swanwick scored 21 points and Randy Kriech 18 as Trabuco Hills High 
clinched at least a tie for the Pacific Coast League championship with a 78-59 
victory over Laguna Beach Friday at Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The Mustangs (16-5, 8-0) trailed, 16-10, at the end of the first quarter but 
outscored the Artists, 27-13, to take a 37-29 halftime lead. Trabuco Hills 
increased that lead to 55-40 at the end of the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Swanwick led the inside game, as he had 16 rebounds. Luis Arenado came off the 
bench to score 13 points and hand out seven assists. 
</P>
<P>
Dain Blanton scored 21 points, Sean Stafford 16 and John Trevino 15 for Laguna 
Beach (8-12, 2-6). 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 86, Costa Mesa 70 -- Senior guard Chris Sheff scored a game-high 
31 points to lead host Laguna Hills (14-7, 6-2). Beau Hossler added 15 points 
and 7 assists. 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 62, Orange 57 -- Woodbridge trailed, 46-45, after 3 quarters and 
finally took the lead with 1:30 left and hung on at Orange. Tom Shanklin scored 
15 and Joe Cohen and Tim Corken scored 13 each for Woodbridge (8-10, 6-2), 
which is tied for second with Laguna Hills. 
</P>
