COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FRIEDMAN IS A HIT AS CYPRESS ROLLS TO 18-4 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Friedman had four hits and four runs batted in to lead Cypress College to 
an 18-4 victory over Chaffey in the first round of the College of the Desert 
baseball tournament Friday in Palm Springs. It was the season opener for both 
teams. 
</P>
<P>
Friedman had a pair of two-run doubles for Cypress, which had 18 hits. Mike 
Neal had three hits. Brett Gregory, Steve Gill and Mitch Kaylor each had two 
hits and two RBIs for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Patterson, a sophomore right-hander, pitched seven innings, allowing seven 
hits and striking out 9. 
</P>
<P>
In a nonconference baseball game: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 7, Southwestern 2 -- Jack Bailey, a sophomore right-hander, 
pitched 8 1/3 innings for the victory in the season opener for both teams in El 
Cajon. He allowed six hits after taking a one-hitter into the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
In an Orange Empire Conference women's basketball game: 
</P>
<P>
