<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALMANAC / SURVEY OF CLERICAL SALARIES: NORTH COUNTY WORKERS HAVE EDGE ON PAYDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Office workers in north Orange County generally are paid higher salaries than 
their counterparts in the south county, according to an annual survey by 
Irvine-based Thomas Temporaries. 
</P>
<P>
Among 15 state urban areas surveyed, north Orange County ranked second or third 
in beginning monthly salaries for three of nine job categories, and no lower 
than eighth in the other categories. 
</P>
<P>
South Orange County clerical salaries were in the middle range of state areas 
surveyed but also ranked no lower than eighth in any of the nine occupations. 
</P>
<P>
South county will see more clerical job growth than north county in 1989, the 
survey indicated. And 46% of the 96 south county businesses surveyed plan to 
hire additional office staff in the first 6 months of this year, the survey 
said, with word-processing typists, general clerks and accounting clerks in 
greatest demand. 
</P>
<P>
In north county, 32% of the 99 businesses surveyed plan staff increases, with 
the greatest demand for general clerks and word-processing typists. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
